## Core decisions

These are not suggestions — they are the visual foundation
of SmardApp. Any compatible client may use its own 
visual language. This file is reference, not requirement.

**Colors**
- Background: #FFFFFF
- Surface: #F8F9FA
- Border: #E9ECEF
- Text primary: #1A1A1A
- Text secondary: #6C757D
- Text tertiary: #ADB5BD
- Accent: #1D9BF0 (single blue — used sparingly)

**The accent color appears only on:**
- Active tab indicator
- New Smard button (+)
- Inline links
- Completed task checkboxes

Nowhere else.

**Typography**
- Font: Inter (Google Fonts)
- Body: 16px / line-height 1.6
- Title: 18px bold
- Metadata: 12px / #6C757D

**Spacing**
- Card padding: 16px
- Card gap: 8px
- Screen margin: 16px

---

## Screens included in Figma

- Inbox — main view, list of capsules
- New Smard — creation screen
- Smard open — capsule detail view
- Scheduled — time-based view

---

## Design philosophy

Extreme minimalism. Zero visual noise.
If an element doesn't serve a clear function, it doesn't exist.

The app should feel closer to a notes app than 
a messaging platform. Clean. Fast. Invisible.

---

## Contributing to design

The visual direction is set by the core team.
Community contributions welcome for:

- Identifying UX inconsistencies
- Improving accessibility
- Dark mode proposal
- Interaction patterns and micro-animations

Open an Issue titled [DESIGN] to start the conversation.

